labels.label: This process group reads the configuration from /tmp/nifi_proj/flow.config and it then generates the flow files with attributes found the JSON file
There will be a route back from the node, as each node removes what it is working on. End condition is the input list is empty.
Looks as the only way to get something into cache is to read it from the content from the flow file.
The goal has been assigned to this fire team. However only a subset maybe able to accomplish the required task, most of this spiderweb of links is creating a load balancer for each possible subset.
Create a busy waiting queue, if a goal cannot be seen to straight away, (or really in a queue of 1) it will go through the node selection process again.

config.comments: To calculate the time a goal takes in the system we need the start time and the end time. This processor inserts the start time into the flow attribute under tmp_goal_start_time, which should be in milliseconds.
If I remember correctly, map only takes a value from the content of the flow, this places an attribute into the content of the flow.
